reviews.text: Ordered pickup and got a cheese and bbq chicken pizzas in the jumbo size. They nailed it on the pick up time and it was nice and hot when we got it home. Overall really good pizza but the crust was just really thick for me. I enjoyed the marinara sauce and it tasted fresh and homemade.

The pizza here is amazing!  I‚Äôm very picky, and this is the best pizza I‚Äôve eaten other than homemade. The crust is light, ingredients are fresh, and the cheese ratio is just right. It is not greasy in any way. We‚Äôd never been here before but bought a pizza to deliver to a friend that was moving and that lived close by. It looked and smelled so great, we returned and bought our family three of our own. Highly recommend!

My family has been coming here for years but I just wanted to finally leave a review because of how above and beyond this business goes for their customers. Every pizza we‚Äôve had over the years has been consistent with superior quality and deliciousness. The owner practically rolls out the red carpet for his customers, and those under his employ wear their hearts on their sleeve. Anyways, here‚Äôs wonder wall

Five stars isn‚Äôt enough! We took our family to Pier 49 Pizza for Family Bingo Night, and I still can‚Äôt stop smiling. I have three energetic boys (ages 4, 6, and 8), and we stayed for 90 minutes of nonstop fun. Every one of us won a prize, and the giveaways were genuinely thoughtful and exciting for the kids. The new owners are clearly invested in creating a welcoming, family-friendly atmosphere‚Äîand it shows.

The food? Absolutely delicious. The pizza was flavorful, the salad bar was fresh and clean, and the prices were surprisingly reasonable for how much we enjoyed. We felt right at home and genuinely appreciated. We‚Äôll be back every Monday‚Äîthank you for such a special experience!

A little pricey ‚Ä¶.  It it was delicious
And it wasn‚Äôt busy
We waited a little longer than expected
Pizza was really good
Husband loved the all you can eat salad bar

detailedReviews.text: I called at 8:30 PM to place a pickup order and was informed everything had been put away, so I responded that so you closed early and was told well no it will just take longer cause everything is already put away. Extremely unprofessional and upsetting, makes me wonder if my pizza is safe to eat...

detailedReviews.author: NoVa Reviewer
detailedReviews.text:
This order was carryout.  The owner of this place has found a real arbitrage opportunity - buy Costco pizza and sell it for 5x the price.  This pizza was SO mid - I could not in good conscience recommend it to anyone.  The other food on the menu must be great for it to have this many stars, or they're giving out free food for positive reviews.  We got Ultimate Pepperoni, Margherita, Cheese, cheesy  bread, and the cinnamon sugar dessert pizza.  First, the pizza literally tasted like...well...not much of anything.  Just really bland, like Costco or Sam's Club pizza.  The texture, the flavor, everything.  Mid.  And for $28 for a "16 inch" pizza, I expect something good, if not dynamite.  This is like cafeteria food.  Admittedly, we are from the East coast, so maybe this is just the non-chain pizza experience in Utah?  The second thing to talk about is  the "16 inch" pizza.  I've noticed in Utah that people don't really understand the concept of the Imperial Pizza System of Measurement (e.g. The Pie Pizzaria has this issue, I've measured).  16" pizzas should be that size after it's cooked.  This 16" is more like a large from Papa Johns.  It MIGHT have been 16" at some point though.
The only slightly redeeming thing was the dessert pizza, which was actually pretty tasty.  The crust was a bit dry, but overall it was good.
RE: the pizza - the kids were groaning and barely ate anything and we all felt gross after dinner.  As is the way of our days, the ordering website (grubhub) asked for a tip prior to providing any service, but that's another conversation.  Here's a tip though: Save your hard earned money and spend it on better pizza somewhere else, if such a thing exists here.  Or maybe just order from a national pizza chain, where at least you won't pay a premium.
